      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773766283225,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Step 3 — API + data model. ",
      "fontSize": 25.70141018641881,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Step 3 — API + data model. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "A427SSNgcqJI_gFuVn2ls",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 460.0121952002796,
      "y": -4113.8055609371595,
      "width": 702.5911882189494,
      "height": 367.1877395972118,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b8n",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1734993144,
      "version": 732,
      "versionNonce": 1624930808,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773766283225,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Before drawing architecture boxes, define\nwhat the system does at the interface\nlevel. What endpoints exist? What do they\nreturn? Then: what does the data look like,\nwhat's the access pattern, and what\ndatabase fits that pattern? For URL\nshortener — key-value lookups → NoSQL\n(Cassandra, DynamoDB) or even Redis for\nhot paths.",
      "fontSize": 32.638910186418826,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Before drawing architecture boxes, define what the system does at the interface level. What endpoints exist? What do they return? Then: what does the data look like, what's the access pattern, and what database fits that pattern? For URL shortener — key-value lookups → NoSQL (Cassandra, DynamoDB) or even Redis for hot paths.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
